 x(t) = C(t) \exp\left[ -A(t)\right] \\ A(t) = \int_0^t a(s) ds 
 C'(t) = f(t) \exp\left[ A(t)\right]\\ C(t) = \int_0^t f(s) \exp\left[ A(s)\right]ds + C(0)\\ x(t) = \left[ \int_0^t f(s) \exp\left[ A(s)\right]ds + x(0)\right] \exp\left[ -A(t)\right] \\ =\int_0^t f(s)  \exp\left[ A(s) -A(t)\right]ds + x(0) \exp\left[ -A(t)\right] 
